methods.getImplementationName:
Get a name for the implementing class.  Useful for abstract classes that implement
 LogOutputAppendable or override
 toString.
 The default implementation is correct, but not suitable for high-frequency usage.

:return: (java.lang.String) A name for the implementing class

text:
Base ImmutableTableLocationKey implementation for table locations that may be enclosed by partitions and
 described by a File.
 Sub-classes should override compareTo(TableLocationKey) and equals(Object) only if they need to
 prevent equality with other FileTableLocationKey implementations.
